    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family of marine bivalves having a radially ribbed shell with undulating edges, and many tiny eyes and feelers on the edge of the mouth; they inhabit sandy sea beds, and can swim by rapidly clapping the shell halve together by means of a single large adductor muscle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
